```julia
function clean_column(col::String)
    return lowercase(replace(col, r"\s+" => "_"))
end
```

This function uses `lowercase` to convert the column name to lowercase and `replace` with a regular expression to replace multiple spaces (`r"\s+"`) with an underscore. The result is a clean column name with no leading or trailing whitespaces, and spaces and hyphens replaced with underscores.
